Name: Caracas
Description: Caracas is the capital and largest city of Venezuela, in northern Venezuela, near the Caribbean.

Name: Coro
Description: Coro is the capital of Falcón state in Venezuela.

Name: Ciudad Bolivar
Description: Ciudad Bolívar is in Bolívar state in Venezuela.

Name: Ciudad Guayana
Description: Ciudad Guayana is a city in Venezuela.

Name: Maracaibo
Description: Maracaibo is the capital of Zulia state in western Venezuela, and is the second largest city in the country after Caracas. It has more than 2 million people and it's famous for its typical music, big shopping malls and beautiful parks. It is called "La Primera Ciudad de Venezuela" (The Most Important Venezuelan City) because of its development.

Name: Maracay
Description: Maracay is the capital of Aragua state in Venezuela. Famous for being called the Garden City, for its large amount of vegetation. It has several tourist attractions such as the famous Choroní town, monuments, museums, and parks like the Henri Pittier National Park.

Name: Mérida (Venezuela)
Description: Mérida the capital of Mérida State, is located in Venezuela, at the foot of the Andes, 15 kilometers from Venezuela's highest point. It is the centre for outdoor activities in Venezuela.

Name: Puerto La Cruz (Venezuela)
Description: Puerto La Cruz is a city in Venezuela's Northeast, in the state of Anzoátegui.

Name: San Cristóbal (Venezuela)
Description: San Cristobal is a leafy, prosperous city of west Venezuela. The city is in a mountainous valley in the temperate green hills of the Andes bordering Colombia.

Name: Angel Falls
Description: Canaima National Park is in the Gran Sabana region of Venezuela, in the southern Bolivar State. The park is a UNESCO World Heritage site.

Name: Canaima National Park
Description: Canaima National Park is in the Gran Sabana region of Venezuela, in the southern Bolivar State. The park is a UNESCO World Heritage site.

Name: Choroní
Description: Choroní is a popular beach destination in Aragua state in Venezuela.

Name: Los Roques
Description: Archipelago de Los Roques is a chain of islands and coral reefs in the Caribbean Sea about 166 km north of the Venezuelan mainland. Administratively, they are part of Venezuela's Federal Dependencies.

Name: Margarita Island
Description: Margarita Island (Spanish: Isla de Margarita) is in the Venezuelan state of Nueva Esparta, off the northeastern coast of the mainland and to the northeast of the country's capital Caracas.

Name: Mochima National Park
Description: Mochima National Park is in Sucre state, off the Northeast of Venezuela.

Name: Morrocoy National Park
Description: Morrocoy is in the state of Falcón in northwestern Venezuela.

Name: Los Llanos (Venezuela)
Description: Los Llanos is the vast plains region covering much of central and southwestern Venezuela.

Name: La Gran Sabana
Description: La Gran Sabana is a region in the Bolívar State of South-east Venezuela.
